                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32583",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Clay -- I'd be thrilled if you would provide a patch and\/or commit a fix. :) Be my guest. :)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-14T14:13:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-14T14:13:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37991",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beberlei",
                        "name": "beberlei",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Eberlei",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think this method should go onto Zend_Loader, plus it can be hugely simplified, for example:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\nif (strpos($path, \"phar:\/\/\") !== false) {\r\n    $path = str_replace(\"phar:\/\/\", \"phar#\/\/\", $path);\r\n    $paths = explode(PATH_SEPARATOR, $path);\r\n    foreach ($paths AS $k => $v) {\r\n        $paths[$k] = str_replace(\"phar#\/\/\", \"phar:\/\/\", $paths[$k]);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beberlei",
                        "name": "beberlei",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Eberlei",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-24T10:51:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-24T10:51:23.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38245",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Actually, searching for phar:\/\/ is a bit short-sighted; we really should honor all stream definitions in the path as well.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-04T05:43:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-04T05:43:52.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38246",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Assuming there are no directories ending on :\/\/ you could probably use the same patch?\r\n\r\n{code}if (strpos($path, ':\/\/') !== false) {\r\n    $path = str_replace(':\/\/', \"#\/\/\", $path);\r\n    $paths = explode(PATH_SEPARATOR, $path);\r\n    foreach ($paths AS $k => $v) {\r\n        $paths[$k] = str_replace('#\/\/', ':\/\/', $paths[$k]);\r\n    }\r\n}{code}\r\n\r\n(code untested, spur of mind)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-04T05:47:39.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-04T05:47:39.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38252",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The behavior was not just phar related, but affected any stream scheme registered in the include_path.\r\n\r\nI believe this is now working in trunk and the 1.10 release branch as of r20904; please test.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-04T08:22:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-04T08:22:53.000+0000"
                }
            ]
